HEADWORD: Prodigality
<hw>Prod`i*gal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>prodigalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>prodigalitas</ets>. See
<er>Prodigal</er>.]</ety> <def>Extravagance in expenditure, particularly
of money; excessive liberality; profusion; waste; -- opposed to
<ant>frugality</ant>, <ant>economy</ant>, and
<ant>parsimony</ant>.</def>⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>prodigality</xex> of his
wit.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prodigalize</ent>⟦br⟧
